<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   CANTON, Ohio -- Timken Co. said it will invest $40 million
at its Latrobe Steel Co. unit in Latrobe, Pa., as part of its
previously announced $1 billion, five-year capital investment
program.
   Timken said it will build a 53,000-square-foot plant to
produce billet and bar products.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Latrobe Steel supplies specialty steel products to the
aerospace, high-performance bearing and other critical
application markets. Timken makes antifriction bearings for
the agricultural and automotive markets.
