WSJ900920-0150
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900920-0150.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Gleason Agrees to Sell Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
09/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   GLE
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
FACTORY EQUIPMENT (FAC)
</IN>
<LP>
   ROCHESTER, N.Y. -- Gleason Corp. said a signed agreement
to sell its tool and mold unit to Gen Cap America Inc.,
Nashville, Tenn., will boost its 1990 earnings. Last year,
the gear production concern earned $2.69 a share.
   The unit, Alliance Carolina Tool &amp; Mold Division,
manufactures tools, dies, molds and plastic components in the
southeastern United States. Terms of the sale will not be
disclosed.
</LP>
