<LP>
   ENGLEWOOD CLIFFS, N.J. -- CPC International Inc. named
Charles R. Shoemate to the additional post of chairman,
succeeding James R. Eiszner, who died Sept. 11.
   Mr. Shoemate, president of CPC since late 1988, had been
elected chief executive officer last month. At the time, he
said he intended to "keep CPC following the strategy" set by
Mr. Eiszner's leadership of the $5.1 billion consumer food
and corn refining company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Shoemate, 50 years old, joined CPC in 1962 and has
held a number of manufacturing, finance and business
management positions.
   CPC's best-known brands include Hellmann's and Best Foods
mayonnaise, Skippy peanut butter, Mazola corn oil, Thomas's
English muffins and Knorr soups.
