</SO>
<CO>
   HYBD
</CO>
<IN>
MEDICAL AND BIOTECHNOLOGY (MTC)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Hycor Biomedical Inc. said it retained Allen &amp; Co to act
as its financial adviser in various investment banking
efforts.
   The biotechnology company, based in Garden Grove, Calif.,
said Allen &amp; Co. will provide assistance in debt or equity
offerings, acquisitions, capital restructuring and joint
ventures.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Richard D. Hamill, chairman, president and chief executive
officer, said the company is "exploring a number of
opportunities including acquisitions" but he declined to be
specific.
   Mr. Hamill said that there is a consolidation in
biotechnology companies and he said the company wants to be a
player. "We want to be one of the acquirers instead of one of
the acquirees," said Mr. Hamill.
