<HL>
   Business Brief -- Home Savings Bank:
   Holders Vote to Approve
   Acquisition by Ahmanson
</HL>
<DATE>
09/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11
</SO>
<CO>
   HMSB AHM
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS, CREDIT UNIONS (SAL)
</IN>
<LP>
   Home Savings Bank shareholders cleared the acquisition of
the company by H.F. Ahmanson &amp; Co., the Los Angeles parent of
Home Savings of America.
   The companies definitively agreed on the transaction in
April; completion, which is expected by year end, is subject
to regulatory clearances. Home Savings Bank is based in
Queens, N.Y.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Under terms, Home Savings Bank holders are to receive
about $25 of Ahmanson stock for each of their shares, or
about $300 million.
   The offer price is subject to adjustment based on
Ahmanson's stock price in the 10 trading days prior to
closing: If the figure is $24.64 or more, Home Savings Bank
holders get $28 a share; if the figure is $16.92 or less,
Home Savings Bank can decide not to complete the transaction.
   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,
Ahmanson shares fell 12.5 cents to close at $15.875. In
national over-the-counter trading, Home Savings Bank shares
closed unchanged at $17.875.
</TEXT>
