It is slated to open early next year.
   Edgar T. Savidge, account manager of Cargill's soybean
processing plant in Liverpool, England, will manage the
Warsaw office, due to open Oct. 1.
   Cargill said the executives will study possible
investments in commodity processing and merchandising,
transportation and agricultural products, among other areas.
   Over the past 15 years, Cargill's annual exports to the
Soviet Union of grain and oilseed-related products have
ranged between four million metric tons and 8.5 million
metric tons.
